data.text: Keep in mind I said 'believe' though I don't 'know' if Nate Parker raped that woman. After looking at the transcripts I can't say otherwise.
Not here to defend Nate Parker. I believe he raped that woman. Yet boycotting a film doesn't cut it support-wise re sexual assault victims.
Let's say as a result of the Nate Parker uproar his film flops, his Hollywood career is over. Was that the sole mission of the outrage?
Is boycotting Nate Parker's 'Birth of A Nation' going to help sexual assault victims? Will it teach others about what constitutes rape?....
The concentration should not be on 'Let's Make Nate Parker Pay' but more on what we can do judicially to help sexual assault victims.
